This paper deals with bibliometric networks, which are commonly used in the field of digital libraries (cs.DL). The paper also discusses mapping and clustering techniques, which are relevant to social network analysis (cs.SI) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper focuses on the field of information science, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SD) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
